OL,3,CWorking in understaffed NHS is leaving
OL,4,Cnurses sick and 'broken', leaders warn
OL,6,FMeanwhile, the poll found 70% of
OL,7,Fnurses are working in excess of their
OL,8,Fcontracted hours at least once a week,
OL,9,Fwith 52% of those receiving no extra
OL,10,Fpay.
OL,12,FOne NHS staff nurse in England told
OL,13,Fthe RCN they developed a chronic
OL,14,Fillness related to stress but could
OL,15,Fnot leave work "due to the department
OL,16,Fbeing overwhelmed and overstretched
OL,17,Fand not wanting to add to that".
